In [64]:
sns.set_style('dark',{'axes.facecolor':'black'})
f, axes = plt.subplots (2,2, figsize = (15,15))

#plot [0,0]
k1 = sns.kdeplot(data=movies,x='BudgetMillions',y='AudienceRatings', \
                 shade = True, shade_lowest=True,cmap = 'inferno', \
                 ax = axes[0,0])
k1b = sns.kdeplot(data=movies,x='BudgetMillions',y='AudienceRatings', \
                 cmap = 'cool',ax = axes[0,0])

#plot [0,1]
k2 = sns.kdeplot(data=movies,x='BudgetMillions',y='CriticRatings',\
                 shade=True, shade_lowest=True, cmap='inferno',\
                 ax = axes[0,1])
k2b = sns.kdeplot(data=movies,x='BudgetMillions',y='CriticRatings',\
                  cmap = 'cool', ax = axes[0,1])

#plot[1,0]
k3 = sns.violinplot(data=movies[movies.Genre=='Drama'], \
                   x='Year', y = 'CriticRatings', ax=axes[1,0])

#plot[1,1]
k4 = sns.kdeplot(data=movies,x='CriticRatings',y='AudienceRatings', \
                 shade = True,shade_lowest=False,cmap='Blues', \
                 ax=axes[1,1])

k4b = sns.kdeplot(data=movies,x='CriticRatings',y='AudienceRatings', \
                  cmap='gist_gray_r',ax = axes[1,1])


k1.set(xlim=(-20,160))
k2.set(xlim=(-20,160))

plt.show()
